Happy Father’s Day to all our friends! 🤍 This is a bit of a sad day for us because exactly a month ago my dad’s father passed away in Lima, Perú (He was named after his father César). 
It has been a very difficult month with a lot of downs but like my dad says “he is lucky to have me next to him giving him love and lots of hugs and kisses”.
In loving memory of my father’s dad César, we can say that he never had a mean bone in him, he was always very giving to others and very protective. We know that he is looking after us from heaven 🫶🏼 and he is our new guardian angel 🤍
We will always remember him with love and a big smile.
Sending a loving hug to everyone who is missing a father today #LoubieFamily

Thank you to @delta crew for always being so sweet with us and all the 🫶🏻 @ladyvagenta ✈️ @skygirl6603 and rivergray5501 
Just a few facts before traveling:
Loubie doesn’t use any medication 
There is preparation before flying like avoiding the previous meal and cutting the water intake a few hours before.
You should meet the requirements from DOT and each country has different entry requirements, check if your vet is approved by DOT to do this paperwork for you.
We learned throughout the years and unfortunately we can’t give a straight answer to your questions since each case is very unique and your vet will be the best person to guide you.
Now, let’s fasten your seatbelts “Louboutina Airlines is ready to take off” 🐶✈️ Puptinis will be served shortly 💁🏼‍♀️🍸
